title: S.J. boys: Kanu sparks Burlington City soccer
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports 
Elsewhere in the Burlington County league: 
Rancocas Valley, which is ranked third in South Jersey by The Inquirer, tied visiting Delran, 1-1. Mike Strohlein scored for Delran and Matt Hannan scored for Rancocas Valley. 
Connor Reilly scored the overtime winner as Holy Cross knocked off host Northern Burlington, 3-2. 
Eric Stuhler scored twice and Pemberton topped host Trenton Catholic, 5-1. 
Damien Jennings and Brett Maute each scored first-half goals to lead host Palmyra over Medford Tech, 2-0. 
Pat McCarthy potted two goals and Cinnaminson scored four times in the first half en route to a 5-2 victory at Pennsauken. 
Eren Ozturk and Isaias Rodriguez each scored a pair of goals, and Westampton Tech toppled Willingboro, 6-2, on the road. 
Penn-Jersey. David Alexander and Mickey Rodriguez each scored twice to lead Life Center to a 7-0 home win over Doane Academy. Anthony Konah, Alvin Paul and Eddie Comse also scored. Freddy Nyekan had four saves. 
Nonleague. Jacob Beebe scored a second-half goal on an assist from Tyler Lipsack for Burlington Township, and the Falcons tied Ocean City, 1-1, on the road. Josh Brown scored for Ocean City. Cross-Country 
Josh Vencius crossed in 17 minutes, 29 seconds to lead Deptford to a 19-40 victory at Glassboro in the Colonial Conference.
